cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the design choices of online social recommendation systems, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves a behavioral experiment on a simulated massive open online course (MOOC), which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of objective measurements of content quality and the discussion of theoretical and empirical literature on optimal aggregation suggest that this paper may also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
